public class TreeNode {
    int val;
    TreeNode left;
    TreeNode right;

    TreeNode() {}

    TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }

    TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
        this.val = val;
        this.left = left;
        this.right = right;
    }
}

public int maxAncestorDiff(TreeNode root) {
    return helper(root, root.val, root.val);
}

private int helper(TreeNode node, int mn, int mx) {
    if (node == null) {
        return mx - mn;
    }

    mx = Math.max(mx, node.val);
    mn = Math.min(mn, node.val);

    int left_diff = helper(node.left, mn, mx);
    int right_diff = helper(node.right, mn, mx);

    return Math.max(left_diff, right_diff);
}
```

    The algorithm uses a DFS (Depth-First Search) approach to traverse the tree once. The helper function receives the current node and maintains the minimum and maximum values encountered along the path from the root to that node. If the node is a leaf node, the helper function returns the absolute difference between the maximum and minimum values encountered. If not, the maximum difference value between left and right subtrees is returned.
